    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA6-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu iravukkuṟip pāṟpaṭṭu āṟṟāṉāya talaivaṉ (EV: iravukkuṟi virumpic ceṉṟa talaimakaṉ āṟṟāṉāyt; ET: allakuṟippaṭṭu āṟṟāṉākiya talaimakaṉ) tōḻi kēṭpat taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what he, who was unable to take part in the night tryst, said to his heart while the confidante was listening.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA6">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nīrvaḷa rāmpaṟ ṟūmpuṭait tiraṇkā</l>
<l>            ṉārurit taṉṉa mataṉiṉ māmaik</l>
<l>            kuvaḷai yaṉṉa vēnteḻiṉ maḻaikka</l>
<l>            ṭitalai yalkuṟ peruntōṭ kuṟumakaṭ</l>
<l>            keytac ceṉṟu ceppunarp peṟiṉē </l>
<l>            yivaryā reṉkuva ḷallaṇ muṉāa</l>
<l>            tattak kumiḻiṉ koṭumūkku viḷaikaṉi</l>
<l>            yeṟimaṭa māṟku valci yākum</l>
<l>            valvil lōri kāṉa nāṟi</l>
<l>            yirumpal lolivaruṅ kūntal </l>
<l>            perumpē tuṟuvaḷyām vantaṉa meṉavē.</l>

        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l rend="indent">If only [we] could get someone going to reach</l>
        <l rend="indent2">the little woman with big shoulders [and] hips with beauty spots,</l>
        <l rend="indent3">rain eyes of eminent grace like the blue waterlily,</l>
        <l rend="indent3">with dark [complexion], a seat of beauty that is like the bark stripped off,</l>
        <l rend="indent3">the tubular round stem of the white lily growing in the water:</l>
        <l rend="indent4">[and] say [to her]<note place="foot">The dative <term xml:lang="ta">makaṭku</term> does not go with <term xml:lang="ta">eyta</term> (a verb taking a direct object), but with <term xml:lang="ta">ceppunar</term>.</note></l>
        <l rend="indent3">“we have come”,</l>
        <l>– she would be very bewildered,<note place="foot">T.V.G. reads, in accordance with the kiḷavi, not the arrangement of a first meeting, but HIS coming at night to HER place: "she would be wild with love".</note></l>
        <l>with many dark sprouting tresses,</l>
        <l rend="indent">fragrant of the forest of strong-bowed Ōri,</l>
        <l rend="indent2">where the bent-nosed ripe fruit of the Kumiḻ tree</l>
        <l rend="indent3">by the road in front becomes the food</l>
        <l rend="indent4">for the inexperienced animal that tosses [it about],</l>
        <l>she who doesn't say “who is he?”</l>
    
        </lg>

